The Chairman of Ifo Local Government in Ogun State, Hon. (Mrs.) Kikelomo Aridunnu Delano, has extended greetings to Christians at this Lenten period as well as Muslims who are also observing Ramadan fasting this month. Mrs. Delano admonished both members of the two religions to eschew bitterness, greed and hatred during and after the fasting. She urged them to love one another, adding that the two religions should preach peace and tolerance. She appealed to Ifo Community to always maintain harmony and cooperate with other groups living with them. Delano also reminded them to cooperate with the leaders both in the state and federal level in order to benefit more from the dividends of democracy where the development will also thrive.